{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Explore Metal 4 games","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC25"},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn to optimize your game engine with the latest advancements in Metal 4. We’ll cover how to unify your command encoding to minimize CPU overhead, scale up your graphics resource management to support massive scenes and maximize your memory budget, and load large libraries of pipeline states quickly.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-254-explore-metal-4-games"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (32 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-254-Explore-Metal-4-games","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games"]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"WWDC25.jpg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg"}],"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png"}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"title":"WWDC Notes","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-209-level-up-your-games","title":"Level up your games","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to make your games shine on the unified gaming platform. We’ll give you a map of the technologies you can use to level up your game and further improve your player experience. Get an overview of the fundamental tools essential to build, debug, and profile your game."}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"alt":null},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/254":{"checksum":null,"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"text":", and more.","type":"text"}],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","title":"WWDC25","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps":{"abstract":[{"text":"Discover the latest improvements in Metal rendering for immersive apps with Compositor Services. Learn how to add hover effects to highlight your app’s interactive elements, and how to render in higher fidelity with dynamic render quality. Find out about the new progressive immersion style. And explore how you can bring immersive experiences to macOS apps by directly rendering Metal content from Mac to Vision Pro.","type":"text"}],"title":"What’s new in Metal rendering for immersive apps","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-294-whats-new-in-metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to get started leveraging the powerful new features of Metal 4 in your existing Metal apps. We’ll cover how Metal enables you to get the most out of Apple silicon and program the hardware more efficiently. You’ll also learn how Metal 4 provides you with new capabilities to integrate machine learning into your Metal code."}],"title":"Discover Metal 4","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-205-discover-metal-4","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-211-go-further-with-metal-4-games","title":"Go further with Metal 4 games","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Dive deeper into the latest advancements in Metal 4. We’ll introduce the new ray tracing features that help bring your most complex and visually rich workloads to Apple silicon. Discover how MetalFX can help scale workloads by upscaling renderings, interpolating frames, and denoising scenes."}]}}}